===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-uk-sink.ogg|Audio (UK)}}
*{{audio|en-us-sink.ogg|Audio (US)}}
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɪŋk|-ɪŋk]]

===Etymology===
Old English ''[[sincan]]''

===Verb===
{{en-verb|sinks|sinking|sank|sunk}}

===Intransitive verb===
#''(intransitive)'' To [[descend]] into a [[liquid]] or other substance or material.
#''(transitive)'' To [[submerge]] (something) in a liquid or other substance or material.
#''(transitive)'' To cause (a ship, etc) to sink.<!--intransitive sense, so not a circular definition-->
#''(transitive)'' To push (something) into something.
#:''The dog sank its teeth into the delivery man's leg.''

====Synonyms====
*(''descend into a liquid, etc''): [[descend]], [[go down]]
*(''submerge''): [[dip]], [[dunk]], [[submerge]]
*(''cause (ship, etc) to sink''):
*(''push (something) into''):

